-- Bonds Reverse Losses as Moody's Raises India Local Currency Credit Rating
-- V Ramakrishnan
-- 2010-07-26T05:48:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/bonds-reverse-losses-as-moody-s-raises-india-local-currency-credit-rating.html

          
          
             India’s benchmark 10-year bonds
reversed losses after Moody’s Investors Service upgraded
India’s local currency rating to Ba1.  
 The yield on the 7.80 percent 2020 bonds fell to 7.68
percent from 7.69 percent earlier, data on the Bloomberg showed.  
